div.p:
IN discoursing of the annual 
      §. 1 celebration of the feast of Christs Nativity, it will, to any that were not contentious, bee thought sufficient, to put him in minde of S. Pauls argument, the customary practise of the Church;
The practise of this Church. And that in this particular Church of England it is of so ancient usage, that we have no other beginning assigned to it, then the same which our stories give of the plantation of the Gospel among us.
